description:
Another of my favorite Burt Lancaster westerns.  Plays a mexican descent deputy sheriff to the mexican side of a white town.  Good action but also thought provoking.

Once again we are reminded that we do not know a person&amp;#039;s past, so you never know/expect the result of ticking someone off.  It is the movie equivalent of a guy in a bar confrontation thinking the other guy beat up on the floor while the other guy already sees you with your throat ripped out and bleeding to death.

Wide screen, color, excellent quality, English only, no subs, avi format


IMDB plot line.
